    <h1>üèÖ Ballon d'Or Overview</h1>

    <h2>What is the Ballon d'Or?</h2>
    <p>
      The <strong>Ballon d'Or</strong> (French for "Golden Ball") is one of the most prestigious individual awards in football (soccer). It is awarded annually to the best male footballer in the world. The award has been presented by <em>France Football</em>, a French magazine, since 1956.
    </p>

    <h2>Creation of the Ballon d'Or</h2>
    <p>
      The award was created by French journalist <strong>Gabriel Hanot</strong>, and first awarded in 1956. Initially, only European players were eligible, but in 1995, eligibility expanded worldwide. From 2010 to 2016, it merged with FIFA‚Äôs award to become the <em>FIFA Ballon d'Or</em>, but returned to its independent form in 2016.
    </p>

    <h2>Number of Winners</h2>
    <p>
      As of 2025, there have been <strong>66 Ballon d'Or winners</strong>. Some of the most iconic names include:
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Lionel Messi</strong> ‚Äì 8 wins (record holder)</li>
        <li><strong>Cristiano Ronaldo</strong> ‚Äì 5 wins</li>
        <li><strong>Michel Platini, Johan Cruyff, Marco van Basten</strong> ‚Äì 3 wins each</li>
      </ul>
      The most recent winner (2024) was <strong>Lionel Messi</strong>, marking his 8th win.
    </p>

